3.00	Maxxum_7000	Minolta Maxxum 7000	The Minolta MAXXUM 7000 (7000 AF in Europe) 35mm SLR camera was introduced in 1985. It marked a significant milestone in photography as it was the first camera to feature both integrated autofocus (AF) and motorised film advance, the standard configuration for later amateur and professional single lens reflex cameras.	http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/en/thumb/7/7a/7K-front.jpg/220px-7K-front.jpg
